headline: Killing of Alex Pretti by immigration agents fuels anger in traumatized Minneapolis
description: Two weeks after the death of Renee Good, Alex Pretti, a 37-year-old nurse, was killed during a confrontation between Border Patrol officers and residents in Minneapolis. Democrats are now threatening to block funding for the Department of Homeland Security, even if it means triggering another government shutdown.

headline: Russia steps up attacks on Ukraine's shipping routes in the Black Sea
Why the Israeli army doubts Hamas can be demilitarized
Rachida Dati's campaign for Paris mayor gets nervous
description: Viral social media videos once propelled the right-wing candidate for Paris City Hall to the top of the polls. After slipping back, she has adopted a more measured tone as competition on the right intensifies.

headline: 'The MAGA movement is divided in the face of Trump's openly imperial ambitions'
description: A significant segment of Donald Trump's supporters is in favor of isolationism. However, most of them would continue to follow the American president as long as he retains the backing of evangelical conservatives, political scientist Thomas Charrayre writes.

headline: Paris Men's Fashion Week: Véronique Nichanian delivers final lesson in elegance at Hermès
description: After 38 years leading menswear for the luxury house, the artistic director presented a final collection that was easy to wear and crafted from sumptuous materials, with leather taking center stage throughout.

headline: The dangerous liaisons of French rapper Koba LaD
description: At 25, Koba LaD, whose real name is Marcel Loutarila, is one of the leading names in French rap. He is suspected by the courts of having financially supported the escape of drug trafficker Mohamed Amra after his deadly prison break in May 2024. At the center of the investigation is the Black Manjak Family, a murky group formed around the artist.

France is considering banning phones in high schools. This school near Paris already does.
description: The Lycée Michelet, a large school complex with 2,300 students, banned mobile phones in its hallways in April 2025. School officials report positive results from a decision made in agreement with the entire educational community.

headline: Generative AI, psychiatry and the risks of self-service therapy
description: Millions of people use chatbots like ChatGPT to share their distress, and the scientific community has warned about the risks vulnerable people face. Generative AI has shaken up psychiatric consultations, fueled tech giants' ambitions and emerged as a credible tool for analyzing pathologies.

headline: 'We were walking in blood': Iran's doctors recount crackdown on protesters
description: From crowded emergency rooms to apocalyptic scenes in Iranian cities, healthcare workers told Le Monde about the violence that descended on protesters calling for the end of the Iranian regime from January 8.

headline: The EU's emancipation from the US requires clarity and resolve
